footer-item.tezblock: tezblock is a block explorer for Tezos an open-source platform for assets and applications backed by a global community of validators, researchers, and builders.

block-detail.invalid-block_text: This block level is not valid.
block-detail.block-height-tooltip: The block height, which indicates the length of the blockchain, increases after the addition of the new block.
block-detail.baker-tooltip: A Baker takes part in the validation of the network.
block-detail.timestamp-tooltip: The date an time at which a block was created.
block-detail.value-tooltip: The total amount of Tezzies included in transactions for this block.
block-detail.transaction-fees-tooltip: The total amount of fees spent for transactions in this block.
block-detail.endorsed-slots-tooltip: A block has to be enndorsed by other bakers, up to 32 bakers confirm that this block is valid.
block-detail.cycle-tooltip: A Cycle is a set of consecutive blocks consisting out of 4095 blocks. Cycles are used as a unit of “time” in the block chain. For example, the different phases in the amendment voting procedures are defined based on cycles.
block-detail.cycle-position-tooltip: The position in number of blocks out of 4095 blocks.
block-detail.fitness-tooltip: Fitness is a metric used to compare contexts. For example, when several blocks claim to be heads of the chain, their context’s fitness are compared. The block with the highest fitness is selected as the head of the chain.
block-detail.protocol-tooltip: The active protcol of this block. The protocol can be changed through the protocol amendment proccess.
